contentrichtext.text: '''IQ''' may refer to: {{TOC right}} == Intelligence quotient == * IQ, short for [[intelligence quotient]] * [[Social IQ]], a measure of a person's social ability compared to other people of their age == Businesses and organisations == * [[Blue IQ]], a South African initiative to develop economic infrastructure for projects in the technology sector * [[The IQ Business Group]], a South African based company * IQ Crew, a [[Circuit City (1949â€“2009 company)|Circuit City]] brand of the test market PC Services department * [[Institute of Quarrying]], international engineering professional body based in Nottingham * [[Augsburg Airways]] IATA airline designator == Media == === Music === * [[Criminal IQ Records]], an independent record label based in Chicago, Illinois * [[IQ (band)]], a British [[neo-progressive rock]] band * [[IQ (girl group)]], an American pop girl group * [[IQ Beats]], a music production company specializing in radio jingles and library production music === Television === * [[Doctor IQ]], an American television and radio game show * [[History IQ]], a game show on the History Channel * [[IQ (Frasier)]], episode 19 from the sixth season of the sitcom Frasier * [[IQ Sapuri]], a Japanese game show *iQ, an episode of [[iCarly]] === Literature === * [[I, Q]] a Star Trek novel * [[I, Q (book series)]], a series of young adult fiction mysteries by Roland Smith === Film === * [[I.Q. (film)]], a 1994 comedy film starring Walter Matthau as Albert Einstein === Comics === * [[I.Q. (comics)]], a DC Comics character * I.Q., a Marvel Comics character from [[Young Allies (Marvel Comics)|''Young Allies'']] === Other media === * [[Intelligent Qube]], a puzzle game for the PlayStation * [[Ivy Queen]], Female rapper == Technology and computing == * [[IQ 151]], a microcomputer produced in Czechoslovakia during the 1980s * IQ is short for [[information quality]] * IQ is short for [[image quality]] * IQ is short for installation qualification as part of the [[V-Model]] * [[Sybase IQ]], a relational database software system used for data warehousing * [[IQ Modulation]], an analog and a digital modulation scheme * Info/Query, a request-response mechanism in the [[Extensible Messaging and Presence Protocol]] (XMPP) protocol * [[.iq]], the Internet country code top-level domain (ccTLD) for Iraq == Other uses == * [[Inuit Qaujimajatuqangit]], Inuit for ''traditional knowledge'' * IQ, the ISO 3166 country code for [[Iraq]] * [[IQ motif containing GTPase activating protein]], a carrier protein * [[Toyota iQ]], an ultra-compact car {{disambiguation}}
